records.addlTxt:
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. 

The Court ordered defendant to serve 60 days in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 2 days time served. The Court granted Huber privileges, pursuant to 303.08 Wis. Stats. for work and church. Court allows defendant to serve sentence on Electronic Monitoring.

Defendant to report by 2/21/2017 by 5:00 p.m.

Court ordered defendant to pay all applicable court costs and fees by 8/16/2017, to be taken from the cash bail on deposit.

Court orders defendant to pay the fine in Case No. 12CM5244. Defendant to pay $100.00 by 2/16/2017. Defendant to pay the remaining balance due 8/16/2017. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.   

Court will allow for expungement if defendant has no new arrests and has paid the fine in Case No. 12CM5244.

Filed;
-Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
-Pretrial Incarceration Credit;
-Sentencing Referral Form.
